to the editor county lines island of dreams delayed april 13 gives a clear picture of the historical and current situation regarding davids island the board of directors of the federated conservationists of westchester county has recently unanimously approved a policy urging the county of westchester to purchase the island now despite the environmental problems that have been identified the island can be dedicated as parkland and set aside in a virtual land bank for public use when the funds can be found to provide whatever cleanup is required public opinion is strongly against private development of the island and we do n't need to waste time and money considering any more xanadu style schemes william lawyer president federated conservationists of westchester county

